net.jadler

Class JadlerMocker

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.jadler.JadlerMocker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StubHttpServerManager, Stubber, StubResponseProvider

    public class JadlerMocker
extends Object
implements StubHttpServerManager, Stubber, StubResponseProvider
    This class represents the very hearth of the Jadler library. It acts as a great Stubber providing a way to create new http stubs, StubHttpServerManager allowing the client to manage the state of the underlying stub http server and StubResponseProvider providing stub response definitions according to a given http request.

    An underlying stub http server instance is registered to an instance of this class during the instantiation.

    Normally you shouldn't create instances of this on your own, use the Jadler facade instead. However, if more http stub servers are needed in one execution thread (for example two http stub servers listening on different ports) have no fear, go ahead and create more two or more instances directly.

    This class is stateful and thread-safe.
